<br>
In high school, I thought the worst possible thing about being sick was being too feverish to move, yet stuck downstairs with the family to &quot;socialize&quot; and being trapped in front of that godawful Kevin Costner movie, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Tin Cup</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Not only is the movie about golf, but a key plot element is Costner taking the same damn shot over and over again.  I hate golf.<br>
<br>
Then, in college dorms, I found a new level of hell:  being sick on your own.  Added bonus of studying and writing papers when nearly comatose:  exams wait for no man, whee.  (Well, later I learned how to pull the strings, but the first year and a half of college was evil.)<br>
<br>
Well, it has taken a bit but the fates have managed to outdo dorm rooms.  Housemates!!!  2 of mine are now carrying on a merry war about who can wake the most people up at once.  One of them is a 14-year-old trapped in an 18-year-old's body (Erin), and has been banging down the door to get in the house at 2 am, and making hella noise while cooking her meals at 3 am, phone ringing at 4 am, throwing cats around, etc.  Well, the 14-year-old trapped in a 30-year-old's body (let's call him Roger) decided he has had enough of Erin's crap, and now wakes up at 6 am and starts making more noise than most armies would.  Roger dries hangers and boots for hours at a time, stomps everywhere, watches History Channel turned almost all the way up, etc.<br>
<br>
I am a couple weeks shy of 21 now and just starting to get my first migraines, with a nice touch of the flu thrown in for good measure.  Superior little me is not interested in justice, but QUIET.  Erin has decided Roger is a little too obnoxious and earlier tonight threw what sounded like a tearing-down-the-house party, spamburgers included.  After convincing her that I was the only one in the house she quieted down a bit, but I think Roger is home and I really fear for the morning hours.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
When worst comes to worst--Kevin Costner golf hell aside--I have always been able to shut down and sleep through most of my illnesses.  I am a child raised in earthquake country and divorces, with experience in big cities and dorms and everything for good measure.  I can sleep through almost anything!  Well, all that has not begun to prepare me for the titanic clashes of Erin and Roger.  Even Roger's conciliatory earplugs don't help.  So here I am, writing this lousy whine at 3 am and elephants are pounding down my head and my door and there's the nice smell of overcooked spam wafting through the house.<br>
<br>
If I am still alive at the end of all this, let me tell you, Roger and Erin won't be.<br>
<br>
